2. Core Library Infrastructure: Processing and Manipulation

While Pandas remains the "lingua franca" of Python data, it is increasingly supplemented or replaced in high-performance contexts.

Data Handling and Computational Foundations

Library	Primary Function	Strategic Value in 2026
Pandas	Tabular manipulation	Essential starting point and standard for legacy code and feature engineering.
NumPy	Numerical computation	The silent foundation for nearly all ML frameworks (Scikit-learn, TensorFlow).
Polars	Fast data processing	Written in Rust; uses lazy evaluation and parallelism to handle 10-50GB datasets.
DuckDB	In-process SQL	The "SQLite for analytics"; processes complex queries locally without an external server.
PyArrow	Columnar format	Essential for data lakes; eliminates bottlenecks in data conversion between libraries.


