6. Visual Communication and Strategy

Data visualization is characterized as the "art" of the process, following the Pareto Principle where 20% of the core visualization types solve 80% of corporate problems.

Visualization Frameworks

Tool	Usage Context	Key Feature
Matplotlib	Low-level/Static	Total customization; standard for scientific publications.
Seaborn	Statistical/Static	High-level interface optimized for rapid statistical exploration.
Plotly	Interactive/Web	Zoomable, hoverable charts; can create dashboards via the Dash framework.

Essential Chart Types

* Bar Charts: Ideal for comparing categories.
* Line Charts: Best for temporal evolution and time-series data.
* Boxplots: Used to visualize distributions and identify outliers, especially in investments.
* Scatter Plots: Primary tool for identifying correlations between variables.
* Heatmaps: Useful for visualizing correlation matrices and identifying redundant variables.


