7. Specialized Context: Health Data Analysis

In the health sector, data analysis is a matter of safety and efficiency. The complexity and volume of hospital data require high standards of quality.

The 4Vs of Health Data:

1. Volume: Massive amounts of data from sensors, electronic records, and images.
2. Velocity: Real-time monitoring needs immediate processing.
3. Variety: Integration of different sources (clinical, social, imaging).
4. Veracity: Accuracy is mandatory; low-quality data in health can jeopardize patient lives.

Conclusion for Professionals: In 2026, the most valued analysts are those who combine the foundational classics (NumPy, Scikit-learn) with modern performance tools (Polars, DuckDB) and AI-driven automation to deliver insights with both speed and statistical integrity.
